# Memory Bank Branches

This project stores memory bank files under `memory-bank-branches/` instead of the
default `memory-bank/` folder described in rule `500-cline-memory-bank.mdc`.

## Structure

Each subdirectory of `memory-bank-branches/` corresponds to one planned feature and
acts as the complete memory bank for work on that feature:

```text
memory-bank-branches/
├── feat.command.restrictions/
├── feat.consistent.provisioning.style/
├── feat.install.kiro.ide/
├── feat.port.kiro.enhancements/
└── improvement.documentation.updates/
```

Each subdirectory contains the standard memory bank files (`projectbrief.md`,
`productContext.md`, `activeContext.md`, `systemPatterns.md`, `techContext.md`,
`progress.md`) as described in rule `500-cline-memory-bank.mdc`.

## Selecting a Feature at Session Start

When following the memory bank workflow and no active feature is obvious from context:

1. List the available subdirectories under `memory-bank-branches/`.
2. Ask the user which feature they wish to work on during this session.
3. Use the chosen subdirectory as the memory bank for the entire session —
   substitute it wherever rule `500-cline-memory-bank.mdc` refers to `memory-bank/`.

Read all files in the selected subdirectory exactly as described in rule
`500-cline-memory-bank.mdc`.

